<p>I'm Using Doctrine ORM 2.5. I want to know if I need to wrap anything other than <code>$entityManager-&gt;flush()</code> in <code>$entityManager-&gt;beginTransaction()</code> and <code>$entityManager-&gt;commit()</code> when trying to Insert\Update\Remove Entities. Because in <a href="http://doctrine-orm.readthedocs.org/en/latest/reference/transactions-and-concurrency.html#approach-2-explicitly" rel="nofollow">Doctrine's Docs</a>, other statements like <code>$user = new User()</code> is also wrapped in transaction calls.</p>